t</p>&mdash; Patrick Wintour (@patrickwintour) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/patrickwintour/statuses/342592238821457921\">June 6, 2013</a></blockquote>  </figure>  <p>From the Daily Mirror&apos;s Jason Beattie</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/JBeattieMirror/statuses/342592243217084417\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Ed Miliband failed to take question from any of three biggest selling daily papers</p>&mdash; Jason Beattie (@JBeattieMirror) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/JBeattieMirror/statuses/342592243217084417\">June 6, 2013</a></blockquote>  </figure>  <p>From Eoin Clarke, a Labour blogger</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/DrEoinCl/statuses/342589675992674304\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Very Happy to hear Ed Miliband join Andy Burnham&#39;s condemnation of <a href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=%23Zero&amp;src=hash\">#Zero</a>-Hours Contracts. They&#39;re a blight on contentment &amp; family security.</p>&mdash;  Éoin Clarke (@DrEoinCl) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/DrEoinCl/statuses/342589675992674304\">June 6, 2013</a></blockquote>  </figure>  <p>From Jonathon Hawkes, a Labour councillor</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/CllrJonHawkes/statuses/342586453307572224\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Anyone who still thinks Ed Miliband&#39;s speech today was about accepting the Tory narrative really needs to read it: <a href=\"http://t.co/U3MNjTYnfK\">http://t.co/U3MNjTYnfK</a></p>&mdash; Jonathon Hawkes (@CllrJonHawkes) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/CllrJonHawkes/statuses/342586453307572224\">June 6, 2013</a></blockquote>  </figure>  <p>From Len McCluskey, the Unite general secretary</p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/Unite4Len/statuses/342597040242565120\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p>Ed Miliband&#39;s speech offer